# PyQt6 Migration — Walkthrough

## Summary
Migrated entire UI layer from **customtkinter** to **PyQt6** across 11 files + entry point. Backend (api_client, process_controller, prompt_generator, srt_parser) unchanged.

## Files Rewritten

| File | Key Change |
|---|---|
| [theme.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/theme.py) | ttk Style → QSS stylesheet (~240 lines of CSS-like styling) |
| [log_section.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/log_section.py) | CTkTextbox → QTextEdit + QLabel status |
| [searchable_combo.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/searchable_combo.py) | Custom dropdown (242 lines) → QComboBox + QCompleter (~55 lines) |
| [srt_preview.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/srt_preview.py) | CTkFrame → QWidget + QTextEdit |
| [config_section.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/config_section.py) | CTkFrame + CTkCheckBox → QWidget + QCheckBox + QSpinBox |
| [projects_section.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/projects_section.py) | ttk.Treeview → QTreeWidget with QHeaderView |
| [actions_section.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/actions_section.py) | CTkButton → QPushButton |
| [settings_dialog.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/settings_dialog.py) | CTkToplevel → QDialog + QScrollArea |
| [product_tab.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/product_tab.py) | CTkFrame (782 lines) → QWidget + QSplitter (~600 lines) |
| [main_window.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/main_window.py) | CTk + CTkSegmentedButton → QMainWindow + QTabWidget |
| [main.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/main.py) | CTk mainloop → QApplication.exec() |

## Key Improvements

### Performance
- **GPU-accelerated rendering** vs Canvas-based
- **Native QTabWidget** — instant tab switching, no `grid_remove` hack needed
- **QSplitter** — native, smooth resizable panels

### Thread Safety
- `self.after(ms, fn)` → `QTimer.singleShot(0, fn)` — Qt's thread-safe scheduling
- `threading.Event` popup pattern preserved for rate-limit recovery

### Styling
- Single **QSS stylesheet** applied globally — consistent dark theme everywhere
- No more per-widget color configs — one source of truth in [theme.py](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/theme.py)

### Simplification  
- [SearchableCombo](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/1.Prompt_Image/1.Prompt_Image/ui/searchable_combo.py#9-51): 242 → 55 lines (QCompleter does all the work)
- No more `pack_propagate(False)` hacks
- No `tkinter` or `ttk` imports anywhere

## Verification
- ✅ `python -c "from ui.main_window import MainWindow"` → All imports OK
- ✅ `python main.py` → App launched, no errors, no console output
